Back when Stiles was in high school Beacon Hills didn't have a crime lab, because they simply didn't need one. Those were the days.
**||** [8.244 words]
Sooooo much fun! Jerakeen had mentioned this fic was in the works in a post and I was looking forward to it. Then, I was on my way to bed when I checked my reading list one last time (you would think I would know better by now) and I knew I couldn't sleep without reading it. Totally worth staying up for and left me laughing out loud more than once. I'd quote part of it, but I end up just giggling madly every time I try to pick out a section, so you'll have to take my word for it. Or, better yet, run off and read it yourself. :D

item.title: Klim: Pitch Design Information
item.dc:creator: splorp
item.description: From the site: “The roots of Pitch are most certainly in Darling. Darling started it’s life as an uppercase-only caption face for the first Klim type specimen. Like National, I attempted to monospace Darling but it was an absolute disaster. It was too delicate and florid, the proportions were all wrong. I abandoned it and looked more closely at existing typewriter typefaces. What I needed was something with the raw material of Darling, the pragmatism of Courier and the warmth of Remington.”
